fields.description: I followed the usual set of steps for removing an old image ({{euca-deregister}} followed by {{euca-delete-bundle}}), forgetting about the fact that eucalyptus 3 requires one to ask it to deregister the image twice before it will actually deregister the image due to EUCA-1227. Now, when I run {{euca-deregister}} on the image's ID I get a constraint violation and the image doesn't go away. How do you kill a zombie image? {code} gholms@istanbul ~ % euca-deregister emi-D65D38B9 --debug 2012-09-06 09:49:17,489 euca2ools [DEBUG]:Method: POST 2012-09-06 09:49:17,490 euca2ools [DEBUG]:Path: fields.summary: DeregisterImage doesn't work when an instance of the image still exists

comments.body:
Confirmed that this is fixed on Eucalyptus 3.3.  

Version of Eucalyptus 3.3 used:

{code}
[root@g-08-03 ~]# rpm -qa | grep euca
euca2ools-release-3.0-1.el6.noarch

{code}

*Test Run*

{code}
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-describe-images eki-94C4374E
IMAGE	eki-94C4374E	precise-06182013-kernel/precise-server-cloudimg-amd64-vmlinuz-virtual.manifest.xml	185153644748	available	private	x86_64	kernel				instance-store
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-delete-bundle -b precise-06182013-kernel -p precise-server-cloudimg-amd64-vmlinuz-virtual --clear
euca-delete-bundle: error (BucketNotEmpty): The bucket you tried to delete is not empty.
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-describe-images eki-94C4374E
IMAGE	eki-94C4374E	precise-06182013-kernel/precise-server-cloudimg-amd64-vmlinuz-virtual.manifest.xml	185153644748	available	private	x86_64	kernel				instance-store
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-deregister eki-94C4374E
IMAGE	eki-94C4374E
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-describe-images eki-94C4374E
IMAGE	eki-94C4374E	precise-06182013-kernel/precise-server-cloudimg-amd64-vmlinuz-virtual.manifest.xml	185153644748	deregistered	private	x86_64	kernel				instance-store
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-deregister eki-94C4374E
IMAGE	eki-94C4374E
[root@g-08-03 ~]# euca-describe-images eki-94C4374E
[root@g-08-03 ~]#

## confirmed bucket is no longer there ##

[root@g-08-03 ~]# ls /var/lib/eucalyptus/precise-06182013-kernel
ls: cannot access /var/lib/eucalyptus/precise-06182013-kernel: No such file or directory
{code}

Running euca-deregister twice has already been noted as a bug - EUCA-6559.

Question regarding this - for bookkeeping do we have an idea as to which git commit resolved this issue?
The deregister in the bug report fails because an instance is referencing the image, there is no change in that behaviour for 3.3.
This is addressed by changes made for EUCA-6559 and EUCA-6962.

Fixed.

{noformat}
[root@c-21 ~]# euca-describe-instances i-902A4520
RESERVATION	r-A1D13DFF	664480406885	default

BLOCKDEVICE	/dev/vda	vol-2C113E38	2013-09-03T10:42:59.155Z	true
TAG	instance	i-902A4520	euca:node	10.111.5.187
[root@c-21 ~]# euca-deregister emi-21844607
IMAGE	emi-21844607
[root@c-21 ~]# euca-describe-images emi-21844607
[root@c-21 ~]#
{noformat}

Tested with both {{instance-store}} and {{ebs}} images.
